Python - Google Class - Day 2

Regular Expressions:

Ref:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kWyoYtvJpe4


1. (dot) - any character (other than new line)

	\w word char
	\d digit
	\s space
	\S non-whitespace
	+ 1 or more
	* 0 or 1

2. searches left to right
3. Code to extract all email address from a text

	re.search(r’\w[\w.]*@[\w.]+’,’what .n@gmail.com is the @')

	\w - word character
	r - raw
	[] - set of values that can be expected
	‘*’ - 0 or more characters
4. Command to know the place where indentation error is occurring

	python -m tabnanny prog.py

5. import os

	os.listdir(dir) -> provides all files of provided path
        os.path(dir)
	os.path.exists(‘/tmp/file1’)

6. import shutil

	shutil.copy(sourcepath, destdir)

7. import commands

	help.command(getstatusoutput)

8.  Avoid giving >python prog.py, in place of ./prog.py

	chmod +x prog.py -> makes it executable

9. Import urllib


urllib.urlretrieve('http://google.com/intl/en.ALL/images/logo.gif','blah.gif')
